<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   NEW-YORK-SENATE (Albany, N.Y.) _ In the hotly contested race for
U.S. Senate in New York, incumbent Alfonse D'Amato and his
Democratic challenger, Rep. Charles E. Schumer, are actively
soliciting the Jewish vote. Jews are courted as a large and
powerful constituency who can make or break candidates in the
state. By JAMES M. ODATO.
