Travis Tritt's 75-acre homeplace holds much of what you would
expect from one of country's rowdiest rebels -- a good lookin'
woman and a garage full of Harleys. But these days, there's a
playpen in the den, while the lady has a fat diamond ring on her
finger. As he celebrates his 10 year anniversary in country music
and the release of a new album, Tritt is mellowing. He credits the
``incredible'' change in his life to his wife, Theresa, and their
10-month old daughter, Tyler. We visit the Tritt's in their Hiram
home, where Travis talks about his wild days, his career in country
music, and the changes he's been through over the past year.
(Longino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
