<HEADLINE>
A SORRY STATE OF AFFAIRS 
</HEADLINE>
   Commentary  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By ROB MORSE  
 c.1998 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ Many are the mysteries of the Paula Jones case,
and I'm not just talking about why she doesn't sic her lawyers on
that plastic surgeon.
</P>
<P>
   In a written brief in her sexual harassment lawsuit against the
president, Jones' lawyers say she ``continues to feel fearful and
embarrassed, and is unable to watch Mr. Clinton or read an article
about the case without experiencing mental anguish.''
</P>
<P>
   Then why don't all Americans deserve a million-dollar settlement
from President Clinton? Why doesn't she just drop the suit, since
she's helping create the articles she reads with such anguish?
</P>
<P>
   Weirdest of all, how come Clinton apparently is willing to give
her money but adamantly refuses to apologize? That goes against guy
logic. Guys hate throwing away money on lost-cause women, but are
always willing to say ``I'm sorry,'' because in guy dialect it
means ``Go away.''
</P>
<P>
   Bill and Paula, I'm sorry.
</P>
<P>
   Also in the ``I'm sorry'' department is the race for governor in
California. During a recent vacation, I had so much time to waste I
actually spent an hour in front of the television watching the
debate at San Francisco State University between Gray Davis, the
Democratic candidate, and Republican Dan Lungren.
</P>
<P>
   Never mind the so-called issues, like whether Gray is Brown (as
in Jerry) or whether Lungren is Reagan. He started off by basically
claiming to be the Gipper, not the Ripper we think we know.
</P>
<P>
   My wife the former surfer had Lungren cold on the all-important
presentation-of-self factor: ``He's a greasy hodad,'' she said,
easily the worst thing one Southern Californian can say about
another.
</P>
<P>
   Never mind what she said about Davis when he said California
wasn't ready for gay marriage.
</P>
<P>
   For crying out loud, Gray, look at the divorce rate. California
isn't ready for straight marriage.
</P>
<P>
   Davis and Lungren offer a clear choice, at least. One is a
conservative who will kill people and the other is a liberal who
will kill people. Oh, yeah, and then they'll teach our children
well.
</P>
<P>
   Also during my recent vacation, Macy's in San Francisco opened
its Christmas displays on Oct. 1, with only 30 shopping days until
Halloween. What ever happened to the Christmas season's traditional
start 30 days before Thanksgiving?
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rob Morse is a columnist for the San Francisco Examiner, P.O.
Box 7260, San Francisco, CA 94120.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
