   &UR; STARTING A SUCCESSFUL HOME BUSINESS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,400 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By BARBARA WELTMAN &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; From ``The Complete Idiot's Guide to Starting a Home-Based
Business'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Home-based businesses are exploding. Young and old,
professionals and hobbyists, singles and working parents are
capitalizing on the technological revolution that has made working
at home a viable option. Steven Jobs and Calvin Klein launched
their businesses from home. Weltman examines the growth as well as
the pros and cons of the work-at-home trend. (slugged:
BC-STARTING-A-SUCCESSFUL-HOME-BUSINESS-(HOME-BUSINESS-WEEK)-NYTSF,
priority code r, category code l and b)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; IS WORKING AT HOME RIGHT FOR YOU? &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,500 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By ELLEN H. PARLAPIANO and PATRICIA COBB &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; From Child magazine &QL;
</P>
<P>
   This quiz can help readers determine if they have the right
personality and work habits to be successful working out of the
home. It addresses how one prioritizes tasks, deals with a
child-care crisis, handles loneliness and more. (slugged:
BC-WORK-AT-HOME-QUIZ-(HOME-BUSINESS-WEEK)-NYTSF, priority code r,
category code l and b)
