<HEADLINE>
CHEESE SOUP, CREPES WEIGH IN ON TASTE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Both of our recipes this week are from the caloric side of the
kitchen.
</P>
<P>
   Peggy Cooper, from somewhere in cyberland, saw the request for
the chocolate crepes and sent the recipe. And the soup recipe, a
creation of Neiman Marcus maven Helen Corbitt, was sent by Sharon
Richardson. Perhaps we'll go on a diet next week _ and then again,
maybe not.
</P>
<P>
   PARTY CHOCOLATE CREPES
</P>
<P>
   Yields 30 crepes
</P>
<P>
   6-ounce package semisweet chocolate morsels (1 cup)
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons butter
</P>
<P>
   1 cup unsifted flour
</P>
<P>
   1 cup sifted confectioners' sugar
</P>
<P>
   4 eggs
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup water
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   Melted butter
</P>
<P>
   Orange cream cheese filling, recipe below
</P>
<P>
   Additional confectioners' sugar for dusting
</P>
<P>
   In top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, combine
morsels and butter; heat until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and cool slightly. In blender container, combine
cooled chocolate mixture, flour, confectioners' sugar, eggs, milk,
water, vanilla and salt; blend at medium speed until smooth, about
2 minutes, scraping sides of container when necessary.
</P>
<P>
   Brush a 6- or 8-inch crepe pan or skillet with melted butter.
When butter begins to sizzle, pour about 3 tablespoons batter into
the pan; turn and tip pan immediately to coat bottom. Cook until
top of crepe begins to dry, about 20 seconds; turn and cook a few
seconds. Remove from pan. Repeat with remaining batter. Spread 2
level tablespoons orange cream cheese filling over each crepe. Roll
up jelly-roll fashion; place on serving platter. Dust with
confectioners' sugar.
</P>
<P>
   Orange cream cheese filling:
</P>
<P>
   24 ounces cream cheese, softened
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup sifted confectioners' sugar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup milk
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons grated orange peel
</P>
<P>
   In large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and orange
peel; beat until smooth and creamy.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per crepe: 176 calories, 12 grams fat, 15
grams carbohydrates, 3 grams protein, 57 milligrams cholesterol,
170 milligrams sodium, 62 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   CANADIAN CHEESE SOUP
</P>
<P>
   Serves 8
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup butter
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup finely diced onion
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup finely diced carrots
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup finely diced celery
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup flour
</P>
<P>
   1 1/2 tablespoons cornstarch
</P>
<P>
   1 quart chicken stock
</P>
<P>
   1 quart milk
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon soda
</P>
<P>
   1 cup processed Cheddar-type cheese, grated
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons parsley, chopped fine
</P>
<P>
   Melt butter in the pot you are going to make the soup in; add
onions, carrots, celery and saute over low heat until soft. Add
flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly. Add stock and milk and
make a smooth sauce. Add soda and the cheese. Season with salt and
pepper. Add parsley a few minutes before serving.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 226 calories, 15 grams fat, 13
grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 48 milligrams cholesterol,
252 milligrams sodium, 61 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   Requests:
</P>
<P>
   Betty Tobin would like a recipe for a light-colored fruitcake
that requires no baking. he mother made this cake in the 1950s.
</P>
<P>
   Christine Allums, Fort Worth, would like a recipe for ambrosia
and also one for baked corn.
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
