<P>
   BOHLS-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ America can breathe a sigh of
relief. Mike Tyson has been ruled mentally fit to fight, which I'm
sure has kept you up nights. I suppose that decision means he is
mentally capable of delivering a maelstrom of fury on another human
being, or sub-human being, for that matter, in a controlled
environment _boxing ring, not a fender-bender on a street corner _
for millions upon millions of pictures of dead presidents. In other
words, he was judged to have full grasp of all his faculties even
as he prepares to relieve opponents of theirs. Only in boxing is
logic totally illogical. (Bohls, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
