<TEXT>
<P>
   JOHN GLENN STORIES THROUGH THE LAUNCH AND RETURN
</P>
<P>
   Here is a day-by-day budget of stories from Cox News Service on
Sen. John Glenn's return to space. The budget begins with a package
for Sunday, Oct. 25 and continues through the shuttle launch on
Oct. 29 and its return to Earth on Nov. 7. If you have questions or
need more information, call the CoxNet desk in Atlanta at 404
526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY OCTOBER 25:
</P>
<P>
   GLENNSEG _ The country starts to become fixed on Glenn's
Thursday return to space. (Montgomery, Cox News Service). 7.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This would work as a Page One piece to reefer to the
following package inside.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AGING _ Glenn will be a subject in several experiments designed
to evaluate the effects of weightlessness on an elderly man. We
detail the experiments and the purpose behind them, talking with
doctors and Glenn about what's going to happen. (Gaffney, Dayton
Daily News). 30. (MOVING WEDNESDAY)
</P>
<P>
   PAYLOAD _ A summary of the experiments being carried on
Discovery excluding the high-profile studies central to Glenn.
Among them is the deployment of the Spartan, a sun measuring device
that will be set loose in space and then retrieved. Also, the crew
will do some work related to the Hubble Telescope. (Gaffney, Dayton
Daily News). 25. (MOVING WEDNESDAY)
</P>
<P>
   GOLDIN _ An interview with NASA chief Dan Goldin, which will
include his observations on Glenn's return to space. (Montgomery,
Cox News Service). (MOVING WEDNESDAY)
</P>
<P>
   GLENNWEB _ A guide to Glenn sites and sounds in cyberspace.
Should include a look at discussion groups and what's being said,
and then list useful John Glenn-oriented websites, including, of
course, the Dayton Daily News site. (Gaffney, Dayton Daily News).
10-15. (MOVING WEDNESDAY)
</P>
<P>
   GRAPHICS FOR THE SUNDAY, OCT. 25 PACKAGE;
</P>
