<SLUG> BC-AUIO-DIVAS22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Divas deliver in electric event
 &HT;    By Miriam Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   An estimated 20 million people watched this concert when it
first aired live on April 14, making it the highest-rated program
in VH1's 13-year history. And certainly this teaming of five
disparate pop singers was, if nothing else, a nearly impossible
visual treat. Surprisingly, in spite of the potential clashing of
egos and styles, this recording of the landmark event is almost as
much fun.
</P>
<P>
   But be forewarned, there are drawbacks: dumb stage patter
(Celine Dion, the whitest chick on the face of the planet, actually
says hi to ``everybody in the how-us''), Gloria Estefan's Las Vegas
lounge arrangements and Carey's out-of-control vocal cords hitting
notes like an unleashed pinball. The solid moments, however, are as
rich as a ``hallelujah'' from the First Lady of Soul. Certainly
Aretha Franklin's presence sets the bar up a notch, and the divas
deliver. Relative newcomer Shania Twain actually sounds better than
the wobbly Estefan (``Turn the Beat Around'') and unbridled Mariah
Carey (``Make It Happen''). Dion picks the perfect tunes for her
over-the-top delivery: Ike and Tina Turner's ultradramatic ``River
Deep, Mountain High'' and (yes) yet another version of ``My Heart
Will Go On.'' But the star of this show isn't even listed as a
headliner. Legendary singer-songwriter Carole King joins the entire
group for a soulful version of ``A Natural Woman (You Make Me Feel
Like)'' that's as electric as the final frenzy of explosions in a
fireworks show.
</P>
<P>
   ``VH1 Divas Live''
</P>
<P>
   Mariah Carey,
</P>
<P>
   Gloria Estefan, Shania Twain,
</P>
<P>
   Aretha Franklin, Celine Dion. Epic. 14 tracks.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   The verdict:
</P>
<P>
   Sisterhood is powerful on this all-star summit.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
