<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Life gets complicated when little sis drops in
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``The Opposite of Sex'' (R)
</P>
<P>
   Writer-director Don Roos' comedy of bad manners tweaks as many
politically correct taboos as it can. Christina Ricci, that dark
blossom of cinema, plays the 16-year-old anti-heroine, who moves in
with her adult, gay half brother (Martin Donovan) and does all she
can to wreck his middle-class life. That includes seducing his dim
boyfriend, insulting his schoolteacher friend (Lisa Kudrow) and
kidnapping the urn containing his dead lover's ashes. Surprisingly,
as the film spins along on its smart-aleck quips, it heads toward a
resolution that's sweet and romantic.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   Other movies written by Don Roos: ``Love Field,'' ``Single White
Female,'' ``Boys on the Side''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
