state Capitols around the nation, particularly in the South.
Republicans and Democrats are battling for control of legislative
chambers from North Carolina to Georgia to Texas. The fierce
competition is an extension of the transformation that swept
Congress in the early 1990s, when Republicans gained control of
most of the Congressional delegations in the South. The off year
elections unfold in the shadow of the 2000 census, making
statehouse races _ and the 36 governors' races _ especially
important since the ground is being laid for the 2001
reapportionment. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30'. WITH
