recently passed to rescue broken-down banks commits several
blunders. It does not require insolvent banks to close. It does not
require banks to disclose losses. It does not require wobbly banks
that accept taxpayer money to lend to creditworthy borrowers _ the
primary purpose of a bailout. By Peter Passell.
</P>
