<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Fulton, Mo.) _ Through a strange convergence of
events, this college town in central Missouri has attained a
symbolic status in the saga of the Cold War that for more than 40
years divided East and West. It was here that Winston Churchill
coined the term ``iron curtain.'' By ROBERT E. THOMPSON. (Already
filed.)
