   CONGRESS-SPEND (Washington) _ New details of treasures hidden in
the $500 billion federal budget deal emerge as the Senate passes
the bill and President Clinton signs it into law. These elements
are tucked into the 40-pound, 4,000-word, pork-laden spending bill
that Congress sent to the president. As in the House, the
Republicans in the Senate are unhappy with the final package. By
Katharine Q. Seelye. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news
file.)
