<P>
   ENERGY-USE (Arvad, Colo.) _ Special Report: Twenty-five years
after an oil embargo proved that fuel supplies were neither
reliable nor endlessly cheap, the United States has given up nearly
all the gains it made in conserving energy. On average, Americans
have returned to consuming nearly as much energy as ever before. By
Allen R. Myerson. (The story has moved in ``f'' news file.) With 4
graphics. 4,500 words.
</P>
