   STARR-HUBBELL (Washington) _ Responding to the repeated
criticism that he has overreached, Kenneth Starr, the independent
counsel investigating the president, asks a federal appeals panel
here to reinstate the criminal tax case against Webster Hubbell,
arguing that it is closely related to the initial fraud
investigation involving Hubbell. By Stephen Labaton. (Scheduled to
move by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
