<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-TALKS (Wye Mills, Md.) _ A troubled peace summit nears
humiliating collapse as Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu
denounces Palestinian leaders, packs his bags and threatens to
leave. By David L. Marcus.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-TERRORIST (Jerusalem) _ The Palestinian suspect captured
minutes after he allegedly tossed two grenades into a crowded bus
station reportedly met three times with Israeli secret service
officials during the weeks in which he carried out other attacks
against Israelis. Byh Charles M. Sennott
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-PANEL (Washington) _ Clinton's lawyers, meeting
Wednesday for the first time with attorneys for the House Judiciary
Committee, accuse panel of designing an impeachment process that is
``like attacking a man who is blindfolded and handcuffed.'' By Bob
Hohler.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
