<HEADLINE>
SPRAGUE, HORNADAY TUSSLE ON RACE TRACKS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By MARK ARMIJO  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Neither Hollywood nor Don King could script a better
ending.
</P>
<P>
   In one corner is Jack Sprague. In the opposite corner is Ron
Hornaday.
</P>
<P>
   But Sprague might as well be Muhammad Ali. And Hornaday might as
well be Joe Frazier.
</P>
<P>
   When last seen six months ago at Phoenix International Raceway,
Sprague and Hornaday were engaged in postrace mental fisticuffs,
each one accusing the other of intentional low blows during a
NASCAR Craftsman Truck Series race.
</P>
<P>
   There was no declared winner off the racetrack. But on it,
Hornaday delivered several knockout punches that Sprague insists
relegated him to a runner-up finish and put Hornaday in victory
lane.
</P>
<P>
   ``He knocked me out of the way (with his truck),'' Sprague said.
``Ron's a fierce competitor and I feel I am, too. We both want to
win this championship. And when you have two guys wanting the same
thing, you're going to have some kind of troubles along the way.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hopefully, we won't have any more.''
</P>
<P>
   Don't count on it.
</P>
<P>
   With only two remaining races this season, including Saturday's
GM Goodwrench Service Plus/AC Delco 300 at PIR, Sprague is clinging
to a teeny-weeny 28-point lead over Hornaday.
</P>
<P>
   And should Sprague manage to fend off Hornaday, it would be a
second straight Truck Series crown.
</P>
<P>
   Should Hornaday overtake Sprague, however, he would add a second
title to the one he won in 1996, when Sprague finished runner-up.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been back and forth pretty much all year long,'' Sprague
said. ``I couldn't even predict which way it's going to go. But I'm
pretty sure it's going to come down to the last race (next month at
Las Vegas Motor Speedway).''
</P>
<P>
   That's fine with Hornaday, just as long as there's no more
on-track skirmishes.
</P>
<P>
   ``After we left Phoenix (in April), we ran into a few more
problems where we wrecked each other,'' Hornaday said.
</P>
<P>
   One of those wrecks occured three months later at Indianapolis
Raceway Park, a crash that sent Hornaday into the fence and Sprague
into victory lane.
</P>
<P>
   While Hornaday's truck was undergoing repairs on pit road, he
angrily confronted Dennis Connor, Sprague's chief mechanic.
</P>
<P>
   Later, after reaching the winner's circle, Sprague was peppered
with boos from much of the crowd.
</P>
<P>
   ``At Phoenix, I thought it was just good close racing,''
Hornaday said. ``I guess whoever comes out on top always thinks
that way. But it takes two to tango and he (Sprague) was just as
much at fault as I was.
</P>
<P>
   ``The thing is one of us drives for (Rick) Hendrick and one
drives for (Dale) Earnhardt. That's two good teams that race real
close to each other.
</P>
<P>
   ``I still say Jack's a good friend of mine, but on the
racetrack, I think he's one of the fiercest competitors out there.
If I start rubbing him hard, he's going to rub me hard. I guess
it's just two hard-headed drivers wanting to win the
championship.''
</P>
<P>
   On that point, Sprague agrees.
</P>
<P>
   ``Are we all even (in bumping incidents)? I don't know if we
were ever even or uneven,'' Sprague said. ``He's got his viewpoints
on things and I do, too. Sometimes, they're not always the same.
</P>
<P>
   ``The bottom line is it's not the Jack Sprague series or the Ron
Hornaday series. It's the NASCAR Craftsman Truck Series. We're both
doing everything we can to win this thing. That's about all there
is to it.''
</P>
<P>
   If Sprague is correct and there are no on-track pinball antics
involving the two drivers and their trucks, Sprague's past record
at PIR makes him a viable candidate to replace Hornaday in the
winner's circle.
</P>
<P>
   Sprague has nabbed three pole positions and three wins in seven
starts at PIR. Sprague hasn't finished worse than third over the
past five races. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-10-21-98 2128EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
