<P>
   MIDEAST-TALKS (Wye Mills, Md.) _ Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu threatens to leave the Middle East peace talks and go
home unless changes are made in key parts of a document on security
already endorsed by the Palestinians. A senior U.S. official terms
the Israeli ploy a crude drama but adds that it shows the
brinksmanship that can be expected during the endgame of the
tortuous negotiations. By Steven Erlanger. (The first take has
moved in ``i'' news file.) With photo. See also MIDEAST-SCENE.
