   ITALY-POLITICS (Rome) _ Massimo D'Alema is sworn in as Italy's
prime minister and appointed an eclectic Cabinet that has something
for everyone: Communists, conservatives, and six women _ twice the
number who served under the departing prime minister, Romano Prodi.
By Alessandra Stanley. (The story has moved ET in ``i'' news file.)
