   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   SMART-GUNS (Hartford, Conn.) _ The computerized ``smart gun,''
which will fire only for its owner, is seen by its advocates as the
answer to one of the strongest criticisms of guns _ that guns too
often fall into the wrong hands, those of children or criminals.
But others _ ranging from uncompromising gun advocates to staunch
proponents of gun control _ question whether the ``smart gun'' is
such a good idea. By Iver Peterson. (The story has moved in ``a''
news file.) With photo. 2,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   BONE-MARROW (Undated) _ Two groups of researchers say they have
found ways to make bone marrow transplant operations considerably
safer and to expand the pool of donors. By Philip J. Hilts. (The
story has moved in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
