   ALABAMA-GOVERNOR (Mobile, Ala.) _ Part of the political legend
of Fob James Jr., the pugnacious Republican governor of Alabama, is
that he likes to play from behind. As the clock ticks down in his
campaign for re-election, his allies are trying to convince voters
that his current predicament simply reflects the natural order of
things. By Kevin Sack. (The story has moved in ``a'' and ``p'' news
files.) With photo.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ Attempting to refute a
central accusation in the government's case, Microsoft Corp.
produces a secret e-mail message from the chairman of Netscape
Communications Corp. seeking Microsoft's cooperation, offering to
stay out of its way and suggesting that Microsoft invest in
Netscape. By Steve Lohr and Joel Brinkley. (The story has moved in
``f'' news file.)
</P>
