<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    22 confirmed dead in Texas flooding; here's a list
 &HT;    Staff reports
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The number of confirmed dead is 22. Five people are missing.
</P>
<P>
   Bexar County
</P>
<P>
   1. Kenneth R. Ludwig, 31, San Antonio, swept away Saturday at a
low-water crossing. Found Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   2. Dora Mun(tilde)oz, 30, San Antonio, swept away Saturday with
Ludwig at a low-water crossing. Found Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   3. 79-year-old woman, San Antonio, swept away Saturday at a
low-water crossing. Found Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   4. Jim Sutton, 55, San Antonio, swept away Saturday on the road.
Found Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   5. Camille Price, 31, San Antonio, swept away Saturday after
escaping car. Found Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   6. Cameran Ormsby, 67, San Antonio, swept away Sunday and later
died at a hospital.
</P>
<P>
   7. Juan Ortiz, 37, San Antonio, was swept away Saturday from his
truck near Texas 21. Found Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Caldwell County
</P>
<P>
   1. Juan Garza, 71, drowned after floods on Plum Creek covered
his house.
</P>
<P>
   2. Dolores Garza, 83, drowned with her husband.
</P>
<P>
   3. Heather Cottle, 11, Devine, swept away in a vehicle on Brushy
Creek near Uhland.
</P>
<P>
   Comal County
</P>
<P>
   1. Robert Scholz, 80, swept away in car at a low-water crossing
in Bulverde. Found Monday, identified Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   2. Frank Smith, 77, New Braunfels, swept away Saturday by
floodwaters. Found Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   3. Miguel Angel Luna Jr., 6, swept away at Alligator Creek.
Found Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Guadalupe County
</P>
<P>
   1. Joseph Gittinger, 34, shocked by a live wire and drowned as
he tied his boat at Lake Dunlap. Found Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   2. Jason Baker, 22, swept away at a low-water crossing. Found
Sunday in Kingsbury.
</P>
<P>
   3. Edgar Bill Brown, 75, found Saturday in a vehicle when
floodwaters receded in Seguin.
</P>
<P>
   4. Charles Franklin Dennis, 76, swept from vehicle at Mill Creek
near his home on FM 2438. Found Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   5. Harvey Risien Sr. , 71, found Tuesday about four miles from
his severely damaged house on the San Marcos River.
</P>
<P>
   Montgomery County
</P>
<P>
   1. Beverly Caldwell, 38, Magnolia, found Monday in the
floodwaters of Spring Creek. A witness said he saw Caldwell trying
to cross a bridge in her vehicle when it was swept away.
</P>
<P>
   Navarro County
</P>
<P>
   1. Mike McCormick, 33, killed Saturday in a Corsicana-area
tornado.
</P>
<P>
   Travis County
</P>
<P>
   1. Jessica Locke, 8, Pflugerville, died Saturday after being
swept away at a low-water crossing near Pflugerville.
</P>
<P>
   Waller County
</P>
<P>
   1. Jose Flores Alvarez, 33, died Sunday after his mobile home
was hit by a tornado.
</P>
<P>
   Missing
</P>
<P>
   1. Devin McCoy, 7, Devine, swept away with Cottle in a vehicle
on Brushy Creek near Uhland.
</P>
<P>
   2-5. Four Bexar County family members who were headed to a
wedding in Jourdanton: Richard Hartman, 47, of Kirby; his
mother,Donna O'Bar, 65; daughter-in-law Jennifer Allensworth, 20;
and her 2-month-old daughter, Mallory Hartman.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
