<HEADER>
A0067 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-ACC-CAPSULES22-CO     10-21 1119
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-ACC-CAPSULES22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Clemson to clash with Duke
 &HT;    By Norman Arey and Wendy Parker
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEMSON at Duke, Saturday, 1:30 p.m
</P>
<P>
   For the first time since coming under fire several weeks ago,
head coach Tommy West defended himself this week. Saturday's 48-0
loss at Florida State was the worst at Clemson for West, whose
30-25 record makes him third in winning percentage among active ACC
coaches. ``I kind of take offense that there's not been anything
accomplished in the overall program.'' ... TB Travis Zachery, who
got in one play in the second half at FSU after suffering an arm
injury, is questionable. ... LB O.J. Childress and DB DoMarco Fox
also might not play, after both sustained sprained knees. ...
Clemson, which had just 119 yards total offense against FSU,
couldn't put any points on the board even late in the game after
recovering a fumble on the Seminoles' 11 yard-line.
</P>
<P>
   DUKE vs. Clemson, Saturday, 1:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Fred Goldsmith has decided to start backup quarterback
Bobby Campbell instead of Spencer Romine in Saturday's game.
Campbell has completed 36-of 62 passes for 369 yards and two TDs in
his last two games. ``We've got to find a way to get some points,''
Goldsmith said. ``Bobby Campbell has always had a strong arm, but
he's had a history of throwing the ball to the wrong-colored
jersey.''... Sims Lenhardt's field goal against N.C. State last
week tied him with Doug Peterson for first on Duke's career list
with 37. ... Running back B.J. Hill leads all ACC freshmen, and is
sixth overall in the ACC, in rushing with 411 yards. ... Richmond
Flowers is third in the ACC in receiving (42-615) and is fifth in
the ACC in all-purpose yardage (130.0)
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA STATE at Georgia Tech, Saturday, 7 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Bobby Bowden had nothing but praise for the Georgia Tech
offensive unit that his team will face Saturday. ``I'm amazed at
how good Tech is, and that comes with another year of experience,''
he said. ``We're going to really face it again this week.''... Even
though tailback Travis Minor will be able to play, the Seminoles
will start Jeff Chaney against the Jackets. ... FSU has committed
only five turnovers in the last five games after opening the season
with nine in the first two games. ... The Noles have passed for
more than 200 yards in 10 consecutive games and 22 of the last 24.
Wideout Peter Warrick is seventh on FSU's all-time receiving
yardage list with 2,124 yards. ...Place-kicker Sebastian Janikowski
leads the nation in field goals per game (2.29).
</P>
<P>
   MARYLAND vs. Georgia Tech, Oct. 31
</P>
<P>
   The Terrapins threw away a chance to tie the game with 5:38
remaining Saturday when true freshman QB Randall Jones tossed an
interception into Wake Forest's triple coverage. The Deacons took a
20-10 win, spoiling the Terps' homecoming. ... Despite his miscues
_ which also included a bad option pitch recovered by Wake _ Jones
remains Maryland's starter. The offense is producing yards _ it
outgained Wake 334 yards to 293 _ but its relative inexperience has
been telling. ... FS Tony Jackson (sprained knee) may be ready for
the Georgia Tech game. ... The homecoming crowd at Byrd Stadium was
just 23,419, not even twice the attendance the night before at Cole
Field House where a Midnight Madness record of 12,317 watched the
start of basketball practice.
</P>
<P>
   NORTH CAROLINA at Wake Forest, Saturday, noon
</P>
<P>
   Coach Carl Torbush suspended starting quarterback Oscar
Davenport for Saturday's game for breaking team rules and will
start freshman Ronald Curry against the Deacons. Curry has been
favoring a shoulder injury he received against Clemson on Oct. 3.
``He wasn't full speed early last week, but he is now,'' Torbush
said. ``We've challenged our offense. We don't want to put him
(Curry) in the situation that he feels he is our whole offense. We
need the rest of our offense to help him out.'' ... Defensive end
Ebenezer Ekuban has had four tackles for losses in each of the last
two games. After recording only six sacks through the first three
games, UNC has 11 in the past two games and opponents have
converted only four of their last 28 third-down plays.
</P>
<P>
   N.C. STATE at Virginia, Saturday, 3:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Long snapper Grant Dorn has been replaced by freshman Brian
Jamison, but head coach Mike O'Cain did not indicate that it was a
permanent move. Dorn, who snapped a ball over the head of punter
Jesse Wade, leading to a Georgia Tech TD, did the same thing
against Duke last week. The Wolfpack hung on for a 27-24 victory.
... After playing five of its first six games at home, State hits
the road for three of its last five. O'Cain's teams are just 10-16
playing away from home and have lost four in a row. ... The worst
of those losses was a 62-14 decision to Virginia in 1996 when QB
Jamie Barnette made his first career start. ... N.C. State's
defense has dropped to 8th in the ACC in yards per game (366.5) and
points (26.5) and is last against the run (198.7).
</P>
<P>
   VIRGINIA vs. N.C. State, Saturday, 3:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Possibly one of the most underrated players in the ACC is
tailback Thomas Jones, who became only the third player in ACC
history to post back-to-back 200-yard rushing games. He ran for 203
yards against San Jose State and 207 versus Georgia Tech...
Saturday, it'll be Jones against N.C. State's Tory Holt. Jones
leads the ACC and is 15th nationally in rushing (123.8). ``Rushing
for 100 yards is hard to come by these days, and 200 yards is
exceptional,'' UVA coach George Welsh said. ... Welsh says there's
much more to N. C. State than Holt. ``(Quarterback Jamie) Barnette
is the key,'' he said. ``He's very much like Joe Hamilton at Tech,
with some option and some drop-back passing. We've always had
trouble stopping N.C. State.''
</P>
<P>
   WAKE FOREST vs. N. Carolina, Saturday, noon
</P>
<P>
   With its linebacker corps sitting on the sidelines with
injuries, Wake Forest must figure out a way to stop North Carolina
QB Ronald Curry. ``We have to patch our team together once again,''
coach Jim Caldwell said. ``We just have to improve our pass rush,
particularly getting to the quarterback. ... With eight catches for
112 yards and two TDs against Maryland last week, senior wideout
Desmond Clark became the ACC's all-time leading receiver with 200
career receptions. Clark also is sixth on the ACC career
receiving-yardage list with 2,530 yards, has caught three or more
passes in 30 straight games and is tied for sixth in ACC history
with 10 100-yard receiving games. ... Senior QB Brian Kuklick has
passed for 200 yards or more in 14 of his last 17 games.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
